# Testing Safety

## Kiosk Tests
Tests tagged `[Trait("Category", "Destructive")]` interact with system processes (kill browsers, cleanup sessions, etc.) and **will crash running applications** on the developer's machine.

### DEVMODE environment variable
The developer's machine has `DEVMODE=true` set as a user-level env variable. Destructive tests use `[DestructiveFact]` instead of `[Fact]`, which auto-skips when `DEVMODE=true`. This means even `dotnet test` without a filter is safe on dev machines.

### Safe commands (use these):
- `make test` -- excludes destructive tests via `--filter "Category!=Destructive"`
- `dotnet test` -- safe when `DEVMODE=true` is set (destructive tests auto-skip)
- `make test-cov` -- same, with coverage
- `dotnet build` -- compile only, always safe

### If you need a specific test class:
```powershell
dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~MySpecificTestClass" --verbosity normal
```

## Web Tests
- `make web-test` or `npx vitest run` -- always safe (jsdom, no system side effects)

## Full test suite
In CI (GitHub Actions), `DEVMODE` is NOT set, so all tests including destructive ones run normally.
